The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Thursday, July 15, 2004 				 Costly chat
																								Berlin, July 14 (Reuters): A German man reported a female chat-line worker to police after facing a phone bill for 5857.48 euros ($7,244) following an all-night flirt session with her.																								The woman calling herself Tina rang the man on his mobile phone. The pair then became locked in a 6-hour conversation.
